cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the synthesis of reactive systems from logical specifications.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as reactive synthesis is a subfield of AI and the paper discusses algorithms for automatic construction of reactive systems.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses algorithms for synthesizing programs from logical specifications.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper deals with the automatic construction of reactive systems, which is an important aspect of software engineering.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses algorithms for synthesizing systems that satisfy temporal logic specifications, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory.
